supervlan-ifattr.description: The interface configuration of a SuperVLAN.

ifattr-flag.description: The interface flag configuration of a SuperVLAN.

inter-subvlan-routing.description: SuperVLAN inter-subvlan-routing attribute status,1 mean IPv4 enable,2 mean IPv6 enable, 3 mean IPv4 and IPv6 enable, 4 mean disable,default value is 3.

inter-subvlan-routing-for-v4v6.description: SuperVLAN inter-subvlan-routing-for-v4v6 attribute status is used to distinguish between IPv4 and IPv6,1 mean IPv4 enable,2 mean IPv6 enable.If IPv4 and IPv6 are enable or disable at the same time,the attribute value is 5,identified as a invalid value.

ip-pool-filter.description: SuperVLAN ip-pool-filter attribute status,1 mean enable,2 mean disable.default value relate to performance parameter.

arp-broadcast.description: SuperVLAN arp-broadcast attribute status,1 mean enable,2 mean disable,default value is 2.

gratuitous-arp-broadcast.description: SuperVLAN gratuitous-arp-broadcast attribute status,1 mean enable,2 mean disable,default value is 1.

nd-broadcast.description: SuperVLAN nd-broadcast attribute status for IPv6,1 mean enable,2 mean disable,default value is 2.

bind-table.description: The bind relation of SuperVLAN and sub-interface or SubVLAN.

sub-interface-bind.description: The bind relation of SuperVLAN and sub-interface.

supervlan-id.description: SuperVLAN ID. Min value is 1, max value relate to performance parameter.
